720480f-a.title: Manhattan: Hudson Street - Laight Street
720480f-a.text:
Hudson Street, east side, south from Laight to Beach St's.,
showing the westerly aide of the St. John's Freight Termi-
nal, erected in 1868. It was demolished about 1930 and
a new terminal erected between West anc Washington Streets,
above Canal Street.
About 1915
N.. 2SAS
H. N. Tiemann, photo
